Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 02:28:43 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix protected admin navigation cache behavior
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

### Motivation
- Client-side Next.js `<Link>` navigation could reuse a stale RSC redirect for protected admin routes and cause authenticated users to be redirected to `/login` when navigating from `/admin` to `/admin/users` client-side.
- The change replaces fragile client-router transitions for authentication-sensitive dashboard routes with full-document navigations and forces request-time rendering for admin user routes to ensure current auth state is always observed.

### Description
- Replace admin sidebar client-router `Link` usage with full-document anchors in `components/dashboard/Shell.tsx` and `components/layout/DashboardShell.tsx` so sidebar items navigate with a full document load.
- Replace the `/admin` page “Users” button `Link` with an `<a href={routes.adminUsers}>` anchor in `app/admin/page.tsx`.
- Convert each user-name detail link on the users table from `Link` to `<a href={`/admin/users/${u.id}`}>` in `app/admin/users/page.tsx`.
- Mark `app/admin/users/page.tsx` and `app/admin/users/[id]/page.tsx` request-specific by adding `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"` and calling `await connection()` before `await requireProfile(["admin"])`, and preserve the existing `requireProfile` guards.
- Add safe Supabase error handling in `app/admin/users/page.tsx` by inspecting `{ data, error }`, logging a non-sensitive server-side diagnostic when the query fails, and rendering a clear admin-facing error message instead of redirecting to login.
- Files changed: `components/dashboard/Shell.tsx`, `components/layout/DashboardShell.tsx`, `app/admin/page.tsx`, `app/admin/users/page.tsx`, `app/admin/users/[id]/page.tsx`.

Protected navigation converted from Next.js `Link` to full-document anchors (explicit list):
- Admin sidebar navigation in `components/dashboard/Shell.tsx` for: Overview, Users, Employees, Employee Activity, CRM, Sales, Inventory, Purchasing, Accounting, HR, Manufacturing, Projects, Support, Reports, AI Assistant, Settings.
- Admin sidebar navigation in `components/layout/DashboardShell.tsx` for the same list of admin items.
- `/admin` page “Users” button in `app/admin/page.tsx` now uses `<a href={routes.adminUsers}>`.
- Each user-name row link on the users table in `app/admin/users/page.tsx` now uses `<a href={`/admin/users/${u.id}`}>`.

### Testing
- Ran `npm run lint` and the lint step completed successfully.
- Ran `npm run build` and the Next.js production build completed successfully with the admin routes present in the build output.
